definitions.definition: Presence of glucose in the blood (which is always true), and ( usually, more specifically ) average concentration thereof over time, and its regulation; in this sense, glycemia is hypernymic to euglycemia , hyperglycemia , and hypoglycemia , and a mention of glycemia is a reference to blood sugar regulation and degree or quality thereof.

main_definition: ( medicine , American spelling ) Presence of glucose in the blood (which is always true), and ( usually, more specifically ) average concentration thereof over time, and its regulation; in this sense, glycemia is hypernymic to euglycemia , hyperglycemia , and hypoglycemia , and a mention of glycemia is a reference to blood sugar regulation and degree or quality thereof.
secondary_definitions: ( medicine , American spelling ) ( occasionally, ambiguously ) Hyperglycemia .
